      },
      "date": "2013-06-28 00:05:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(65 inline comments)\n\nI would still like to see more integration between this new checksumming code and the existing code.  I'm fine with changing the structure of the existing code to match this new code better, but I dislike having two completely separate code paths for the different checksum types.\n\nI would also like the Lustre DIF handling be similar to how the kernel handles it internally, so that we don't have to re-do this all when the patch is landed into the upstream kernel.  It seems we are doing this differently in different layers (sometimes on the page, sometimes in a separate array).\n\nSome other style issues, but also some real defects found during inspection as well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
