          "date": "2013-04-13 21:10:32.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-2584 data: T10 DIF/DIX integrity support",
        "message": "LU-2584 data: T10 DIF/DIX integrity support\n\nThis patch implements Lustre end-to-end integrity\nsupport with T10 DIF/DIX:\n1) on write, CRCs are calculated on the client,\ntransferred over wire, stored on disk;\n2) on read, CRCs are read from disk,\ntransferred over wire, checked on the client.\n\nWith protocol A (inpill), CRCs are packed in RPC.\nWith protocol B (inbulk), CRCs are packed in bulk.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andrew Perepechko <andrew_perepechko@xyratex.com>\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-286\nChange-Id: I38c3a346763ae1593e6bb950f2590ec0dc7bddde\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
